author: By     MarketWatch
title: Video: Jamestown colony leaders’ remains unearthed after 400 years
text: Jamestown settlers identified after 400 years (2:07) Archaeologists have uncovered the human remains of four of the earliest leaders of the English colony that would become America, buried for more than 400 years near the altar of what was America's first Protestant church in Jamestown, Va. Photo: Smithsonian.
